##Oral Record | delivery boy to solve the Golden Pool of medical problems: I sent not express, is the life-saving People Ah!

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

I can save 4 hours a day by taking a paramedic to and from the hospital. 100 TRIPS IS 400 hours. 400 hours. I can save as many people as the paramedic can save.

Oral | Wang Yong

Sorting out the snow in Eastern Wu

I'm a delivery man and a game-changer.

At 5 a.m. on Feb. 13, I woke up in a high and low bed at the Wuhan Second Ring Road Express Delivery Warehouse, a somewhat special warehouse built right at the mouth of a sewer pipe. It was damp and cold. I picked up a thermometer and took my temperature, which was no more than 36 degrees. I checked my phone calendar before I left, and it turns out, I haven't been home in 22 days.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
These days, Wang Yong has been living in the company warehouse

I am Wang Yong, grew up in Wuhan, is an ordinary 80 after express delivery boy, from morning to night, delivery, packing, hair express, moving goods, day after day of Struggle, enough to a family of three expenses. Every day I wake up into the battle, like a wind-up "top. ". In early February, I was approached by a succession of reporters, never expecting to be in the news during this epidemic.

The nurse came home, and she cried the whole way

Things to start from the New Year's Eve, because of the impact of the epidemic, the courier company has a holiday. In the evening, I closed the warehouse and returned home with family reunion dinner. At 10:00 in the evening, while trying to coax his daughter to rest, he suddenly brushed a friend circle of a nurse from Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital, "For help, we have no buses or subways, we can't go home, it takes four hours to walk home, " the person wrote. The request was issued at 6 o'clock, and no one has been picking up the order.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wang Yong in a hazmat suit

"Yes or no" was a struggle, but I wanted to do it. I did not dare to tell my family that I had spent an hour on my own in silence. Finally decided to "go" . The wife is a psychologically fragile person, has not experienced what big matter; the parents are also old, can not let them worry. So I decided to go it alone, as if I had lied to them in good faith.

The first question is how to get out? The nurse who issued the bill got off the night shift at six o'clock the next morning. I told my wife that I needed the staff on duty temporarily. I was assigned to the duty and got away with it successfully. Without any protective equipment in hand, I went to the supermarket to buy two N95 masks and arrived at Jinyintan hospital at 6 o'clock. The nurse saw me for a moment and said, "I didn't think anyone would take this. " Then she got into the car and sobbed silently all the way to the exit.

The first day I took nearly thirty medical staff to and from the hospital, one day down, legs shaking. To be honest, I was scared. What if it got infected. I began to beat a retreat and said to myself, "forget it. " But when I saw a nurse at night, the destination is dozens of kilometers away from the hospital, no one to pick up. And then he changed his mind.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I made up a second "Lie" and told my wife that I had contact with suspected patients, afraid of being infected, can only sleep in the express warehouse temporary isolation for 7 days, no problem can go home. At first, my wife didn't listen to my explanation. She cried her eyes out. Later, when she was stable, she agreed. And gradually, with more contact with the medical staff, I began to understand why they would rather walk home than take a break.

In fact, in the week before the National Medical Rescue Team arrived, the gold and silver team worked all night, 10 percent of them sleeping in beds and the rest in chairs; the patients'groans and walkie talkies hovered 24 hours a day, staying in such an atmosphere is too much for anyone to bear mentally, let alone get a good night's rest. So even a four-hour walk is a short break for them.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Medics take a short break in their armchairs

On the fourth day of the Lunar New Year, more and more medical teams are supporting Wuhan, like giving them a shot in the arm. That day, I was supposed to take a doctor to work, when suddenly I got a phone call from her: "Master, you don't have to pick me up, I can take a rest today. " I was very happy, and the Medical Service Group I built was getting more and more people in, i began to realize that no matter how hard I tried, I could only meet the requirements of a 300-kilometer-a-day shuttle.

To recruit volunteers to ride with the paramedics

So I started posting on my friends'network asking for volunteers, demanding that I live alone and wear protective gear. If the answer is no, I refuse them. Next, 20 or 30 people took turns to follow me. In the middle of the race, we broke three cars. Later, six cars could basically meet the demand. But it's still not a long-term solution, and it's been suggested that resources could be found.

First we got in touch with mobike. Their delivery efficiency was very fast. All the points in hospitals and hotels, vehicle personnel were in place in one day, which solved the travel demand of about 2 kilometers, it takes a long time. It takes a week. In order to meet the travel demand of medical staff in Jinyintan Hospital outside the Third Ring Road, Didi changed the number of receiving single kilometers from within 3.5 kilometers to within 15 kilometers.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Green Tangerine Bicycle set up service point on Panlong Bridge

Green Orange Bicycle is also three days to complete docking, put 400 sets, from the operation and maintenance, cost, put, a dedicated team management, all of a sudden completely solve the travel problem. Those days, every night, I had to set aside an hour, and family video acting, friends posted recruitment and help to my family not open information, but as the number of trips, the task more busy, this matter can no longer be hidden. My wife was in a panic when she found out, so I did some thinking work, and I ended up being supportive.

It's just that my two-year-old daughter is very clingy to me. At night, she clamors to sleep with her father and sits in the corner crying if she can't find her. Lantern Festival that day, looking at her prone in my photo kiss and kiss the video, feel particularly guilty, miss their families.

But I understand that I can not stop. The medical team that came to Wuhan is our "lifesaver. " The government has arranged for them to have food and a place to live, but the details may not be taken care of. We can make up the gaps and omissions, and do everything I can to make it worth their while.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Wang Yong family

Wang Yong's daughter saw her father's photo and kissed him

For Rice, we settled on a restaurant

At first we raised 22,000 yuan to provide instant noodles and water for the night shift doctors. Then one of the nurses sent out a friend circle saying, I really want to eat rice, I saw after the heart is broken, determined to let them eat white rice the next day, soon there are restaurant owners docking, 16 yuan a piece, a day more than 100 pieces. The next day, I was approached by a restaurant owner in Wuhan who offered me 1,500 meals a day, free of charge, to Golden Pond Hospital, Xinhua Hospital and Concord Hospital.

The dining problem was solved, but I found another new situation: the docking restaurant was overloaded and capacity was already at its peak. I began to wonder if we could have a dedicated dining room, given the many resources available. I soon began to land implementation, a day to run more than 20 restaurants to talk about cooperation, one by one asked whether we could use the venue and staff for free or at a low price, and soon, the owner of the Fuming Mountain restaurant, with our goal, hit it off.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Fuming Mountain restaurant offers free meals

February 5, the Fuming Mountain restaurant began to serve food, two meat and one vegetable, soon met the Golden Lake Hospital dining problem. The rest of the production, 240 per day for Didi drivers, since others are here to help us, we should no longer graft the risk onto others. Unfortunately, on Feb. 7, local food safety authorities in Wuhan shut down the restaurant and demanded that it be closed.

The reason is that during the critical period of the epidemic, only a few designated units are allowed to produce meals, and this qualification can not be applied for at present. Communication failed a day, but under, we contacted several fixed-point service units, found each other said a box of rice cost 40 yuan, we raised funds simply can not afford.

I was frustrated, but then things started to turn around. A local business in Wuhan, called Today convenience store, solved the dining problem by providing meals to all the support teams at Jinyintan hospital and 300 free lunches for Didi owners every day. That day, I was relieved.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
That the Today store supplies to the medical staff

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Free boxed lunch from Today's convenience store

I don't have any resources, but it hits the fan

I am a person without any resources, but along the way, special thanks to the support of the following volunteers and large enterprises. Everybody's working on this. I'm just the guy running the show. Going out, eating -- each set set I put under one person's control, freeing up my hands to do other things. Because of the daily contact with the medical staff, their status I know the most, life support is essential.

For example, glasses broken, broken mobile phone screen, need to buy slippers, nail clippers, chargers and even long Johns, in the group through the long cry, soon have someone to buy, to help them deal with. I remember one time when two doctors of the Shanghai medical team had a birthday party and we bought them a cake and had a memorable birthday. Another time, because the air conditioning in the hospital could not be turned on, the most needed medical care was a sleeveless down jacket to keep them warm, we bought every piece of Shang Chao's down jacket and ordered 1,000 pieces of Uniqlo in Guangzhou.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Volunteer Barber, master Gan, has been on duty five times and received rave reviews

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wang Yong in the group docking service Anhui Assistance Wuhan Intensive Care Group

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wang Yong organized volunteers to buy a birthday cake for the Shanghai medical team

One of the things that impressed me most was that the medical staff needed a batch of protective shoe covers, and the whole of Wuhan was out of stock. Later, I found a shop on Taobao that had them, but at GE store in Ezhou, 55 kilometers from the city of Wuhan, because the businessman is also a new coronary pneumonia confirmed patients, can not send express delivery. I drove all night to pick them up and brought back 2,000 pairs.

I do things day in and day out, solving problems, I don't know when I'll stop, but I'm always there when the paramedics call me. Up to now, we have a total of 1,000 medical personnel docking, and the next docking 3000 well-known medical team in Wuhan.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On Feb. 2, Wang Yong posted a message on his friends'circle, saying, I have been able to hold it for so many days, but the concern of a nurse made me cry

A man can't come across such a big thing in his life. No matter what he does, he does it with all his strength and without regret. When I think about it, the reason I started this was simple: I could save four hours a day by taking one paramedic to and from the hospital, and I could save 400 hours by taking 100, and I could save as many people as the paramedic could save.

On the night of February 13, my mother's friends saw my video and called her to show their support. In the eyes of my relatives and friends, I was never an easy child. Even now, my parents are still worried about me, helping me take care of the children, and supporting my family. Fortunately, I didn't embarrass you in this affair.
